<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<title>People Lookup Site</title>
	<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
</head>
<body>
	<% if (err) { %>
		<h1 class="err"><%= err %></h1>
	<% } %>
	<h1>Criminal Record Lookup</h1>
	<p>Here you can find some extremely <del>il</del>legitimate records of peoples' criminal activity! And it's completely free of charge! <span class="small">Just give me a million dollars first otherwise I'll only let you see their names.</span> My friend dropped all the tables but I made sure it won't happen again! In fact, I'm so confident in my website writing abilities that I'll give you <a href="/src">the source</a> so you can see how secure my site is!</p>
	<div class="searchdiv">
		<input id="searchbar" placeholder="John"/>
		<button id="searchbutton">üîç</button>
	</div>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Name</th>
				<th>Criminal Record</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<% results.forEach(function(r) { %>
				<tr><td><%= r.name %></td><td>where's my million dollars</td></tr>
			<% }); %>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<script>
		searchbutton.addEventListener("click", function() {
			location.search = "?q=" + encodeURIComponent(searchbar.value);
		});
		searchbar.addEventListener("keydown", function(e) {
			if (e.code == "Enter") {
				location.search = "?q=" + encodeURIComponent(searchbar.value);
			}
		})
	</script>
</body>
</html>
